      • getStringAttribute

        public static String getStringAttribute(String attrName,
                                        IHasAttributes attributeHolder,
                                        String defaultValue)
        Retrieves and returns the attribute with the specified name from the specified attribute holder as a String value, using the specified default value if the attribute value is missing, null, or otherwise empty.

        If the attribute value is not null, it is converted to a String by calling toString() on the attribute value. If the resulting String is not null or empty it is returned, otherwise the specified default value is returned.

        Parameters:
        attrName - the name of the attribute to retrieve
        attributeHolder - the object to search
        defaultValue - the default value to use
        Returns:
        the String conversion of the attribute value

      • getStringArrayAttribute

        public static String[] getStringArrayAttribute(String attrName,
                                               IHasAttributes attributeHolder,
                                               String[] defaultValue)
                                        throws BadDataException
        Retrieves and returns the attribute with the specified name from the specified attribute holder as an array of String values. The value in of the attribute should be a comma delimited string or a String[] object. If it is a string then each element in the array is also trimmed of leading and trailing whitespace. If that value of the attribute is null then null is returned. If it is empty string, then an empty array will be returned.
        Parameters:
        attrName - the name of the attribute to retrieve
        attributeHolder - the object to search
        defaultValue - the default value to return if the attribute is missing
        Returns:
        an array of strings
        Throws:
        BadDataException - if the attribute value is not a String[] or String

      • getRequiredStringArrayAttribute

                                                       IHasAttributes attributeHolder)
                                                throws BadDataException,
                                                       MissingDataException
        Retrieves and returns the attribute with the specified name from the specified attribute holder as an array of String values. The value in of the attribute should be a comma delimited string or a String[] object. If it is a string then each element in the array is also trimmed of leading and trailing whitespace. If that value of the attribute is null then null is returned. If it is empty string, then an empty array will be returned.
        Parameters:
        attrName - the name of the attribute to retrieve
        attributeHolder - the object to search
        Returns:
        an array of strings
        Throws:

      • getBooleanAttribute

        public static boolean getBooleanAttribute(String attrName,
                                          IHasAttributes attributeHolder,
                                          boolean defaultValue)
                                   throws BadDataException
        Retrieves and returns the attribute with the specified name from the specified attribute holder as a boolean value, using the specified default value if the attribute value is missing, null, or otherwise empty.

        If the attribute value is a String and is not one of the recognized truths or untruths, or if the attribute value cannot otherwise be converted to a boolean, a BadDataException is thrown.

        Parameters:
        attrName - the name of the attribute to retrieve
        attributeHolder - the object to search
        defaultValue - the default value to use
        Returns:
        the boolean conversion of the attribute value
        Throws:
        BadDataException - if the attribute value is not a boolean

      • getStringAttributeAsEnum

        public static <T extends Enum<T>> T getStringAttributeAsEnum(String attrName,
                                                             IHasAttributes attributeHolder,
                                                             String defaultValue,
                                                             Class<T> enumType)
        Returns an attribute value from the specified attribute holder as an enum.

        If the attribute value is not null, it's converted to an enum. Otherwise the specified default value is returned.

        Attribute values must be in lower camel case, and enum constants must be in upper underscore case.

        Type Parameters:
        T - enum type
        Parameters:
        attrName - the name of the attribute to retrieve
        attributeHolder - the object to search
        defaultValue - the default value
        enumType - target enum type
        Returns:
        the attribute value as an enum
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a matching enum constant cannot be found
